mate and uncompromising 1972 masterpiece \u003ci\u003ePink Moon\u003c/i\u003e, was named by \u003ci\u003eRolling Stone\u003c/i\u003e on its list of the 500 Greatest Albums of All Time.\\n∙ His album sales increased significantly after the whimsical, melancholy folk song “Pink Moon” was used in a 1999 national automotive ad campaign.\\n∙ Lucinda Williams and Beck covered his stripped-down song “Which Will,” while Norah Jones has put a jazz-influenced spin on his “Day Is Done.”\\n∙ Reissues of 1971’s \u003ci\u003eBryter Layter\u003c/i\u003e and 1972’s \u003ci\u003ePink Moon\u003c/i\u003e both entered \u003ci\u003eBillboard\u003c/i\u003e’s Vinyl Albums chart in 2013.\\n∙ In 2017, \u003ci\u003eQ\u003c/i\u003e magazine included his first album, 1969’s \u003ci\u003eFive Leaves Left\u003c/i\u003e, on their list of Debut Albums That Changed Music.\",\"isGroup\":false,\"bornOrFormed\":\"June 19, 1948\",\"name\":\"Nick Drake\",\"editorialArtwork\":{}},\"views\":{\"live-albums\":{\"href\":\"/v1/catalog/us/artists/1285818/view/live-albums?l=en-US\",\"attributes\":{\"title\":\"Live Albums\"},\"data\":[]},\"featured-release\":{\"href\":\"/v1/catalog/us/artists/1285818/view/featured-release?l=en-US\",\"attributes\":{\"title\":\"Featured Release\"},\"data\":[]},\"featured-albums\":{\"href\":\"/v1/catalog/us/artists/1285818/view/featured-albums?l=en-US\",\"attributes\":{\"title\":\"Essential Albums\"},\"data\":[{\"id\":\"1440758653\",\"type\":\"albums\",\"href\":\"/v1/catalog/us/albums/1440758653?l=en-US\",\"attributes\":{\"artwork\":{\"width\":1423,\"height\":1411,\"url\":\"https://is3-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music128/v4/56/08/f3/5608f39a-6efc-a799-d4b8-b0da30acf1da/00042284292320.rgb.jpg/{w}x{h}bb.jpeg\",\"bgColor\":\"1a3320\",\"textColor1\":\"dadfc1\",\"textColor2\":\"95c77f\",\"textColor3\":\"b4bca1\",\"textColor4\":\"7ca96c\"},\"artistName\":\"Nick Drake\",\"url\":\"https://music.apple.com/us/album/pink-moon-remastered/1440758653\",\"trackCount\":11,\"releaseDate\":\"1972-02-25\",\"name\":\"Pink Moon ((Remastered))\",\"artistUrl\":\"https://music.apple.com/us/artist/nick-drake/1285818\",\"editorialArtwork\":{\"originalFlowcaseBrick\":{\"width\":1778,\"height\":600,\"url\":\"https://is4-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Features5/v4/58/99/46/589946c6-62a3-eb33-4a29-1805a7c3939c/source/{w}x{h}bb.jpeg\",\"bgColor\":\"16311e\",\"textColor1\":\"99dbad\",\"textColor2\":\"7ed9b8\",\"textColor3\":\"7fb990\",\"textColor4\":\"69b799\"}},\"playParams\":{\"id\":\"1440758653\",\"kind\":\"album\"},\"editorialNotes\":{\"standard\":\"Whereas Nick Drake's earlier albums boasted elegant orchestrations, his final collection—perhaps his most potent of all—is the soul of minimalism. On tunes stripped to their bare essentials, both sonically and structurally, Drake's haunted murmur is accompanied only by his acoustic guitar. Desperation drips from the trenchant lyrics of tunes like \\\"Things Behind the Sun\\\" and \\\"Place to Be,\\\" as Drake practically whispers his words, like a man struggling to fortify himself while facing the abyss.\",\"short\":\"The stunning, spooky swan song of a once-in-a-lifetime talent.\"}}},{\"id\":\"1440656068\",\"type\":\"albums\",\"href\":\"/v1/catalog/us/albums/1440656068?l=en-US\",\"attributes\":{\"artwork\":{\"width\":1423,\"height\":1411,\"url\":\"https://is3-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music128/v4/98/8d/65/988d652e-f112-2354-4880-6fecc35b8fa8/00042284291521.rgb.jpg/{w}x{h}bb.jpeg\",\"bgColor\":\"277431\",\"textColor1\":\"fffff6\",\"textColor2\":\"eaf3ac\",\"textColor3\":\"d3e3ce\",\"textColor4\":\"c3da94\"},\"artistName\":\"Nick Drake\",\"url\":\"https://music.apple.com/us/album/five-leaves-left-remastered/1440656068\",\"trackCount\":10,\"releaseDate\":\"1970-01-01\",\"name\":\"Five Leaves Left ((Remastered))\",\"artistUrl\":\"https://music.apple.com/us/artist/nick-drake/1285818\",\"editorialArtwork\":{},\"playParams\":{\"id\":\"1440656068\",\"kind\":\"album\"},\"editorialNotes\":{\"standard\":\"The haunting songs of Nick Drake continue to fascinate fans worldwide over 30 years after his untimely death. Beneath his music's delicately melodic surface are depths of emotion and insight few singer-songwriters have approached. \u003ci\u003eFive Leaves Left\u003c/i\u003e, his 1969 debut, was recorded while Drake was still a student at Cambridge University. As a singer, he displays self-assurance far beyond his years, combining folk influences with jazz-tinged phrasing. Such tracks as \\\"Way to Blue,\\\" \\\"River Man\\\" and \\\"Saturday Sun\\\" capture longing and loss in moody watercolor tones. \\\"Time Has Told Me\\\" and \\\"Thoughts of Mary Jane\\\" are evocative love songs, while \\\"Fruit Tree\\\" ponders the price of fame.  Produced by folk-rock maven Joe Boyd, the album's tracks are enhanced by Richard Thompson's tasteful guitar and Robert Kirby's inspired orchestrations.  A timelessly beguiling work, \u003ci\u003eFive Leaves Left\u003c/i\u003e is the luminous first creation of an artist destined to become a legend. \"}}}]},\"latest-release\":{\"href\":\"/v1/catalog/us/artists/1285818/view/latest-release?l=en-US\",\"attributes\":{\"title\":\"Latest Release\"},\"data\":[]},\"top-songs\":{\"href\":\"/v1/catalog/us/artists/1285818/view/top-songs?l=en-US\",\"next\":\"/v1/catalog/us/artists/1285818/view/top-songs?l=en-US\u0026offset=20\",\"attributes\":{\"title\":\"Top Songs\"},\"data\":[{\"id\":\"1440758657\",\"type\":\"songs\",\"href\":\"/v1/catalog/us/songs/1440758657?l=en-US\",\"attributes\":{\"previews\":[{\"url\":\"https://audio-ssl.itunes.apple.com/itunes-assets/AudioPreview128/v4/26/c6/b5/26c6b5b8-8d39-ec95-26eb-a55795722a17/mzaf_2309265247699736741.plus.aac.p.m4a\"}],\"artwork\":{\"width\":1423,\"height\":1411,\"url\":\"https://is3-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music128/v4/56/08/f3/5608f39a-6efc-a799-d4b8-b0da30acf1da/00042284292320.rgb.jpg/{w}x{h}bb.jpeg\",\"bgColor\":\"1a3320\",\"textColor1\":\"dadfc1\",\"textColor2\":\"95c77f\",\"textColor3\":\"b4bca1\",\"textColor4\":\"7c