piano chords.\",\"short\":\"Mellow ballads and piano jams that view love and life from all angles.\"},\"description\":{\"standard\":\"In the wake of the Summer of Love, troubadours turned their attention inward and upward, using their ample talents to champion causes both romantic and existential. The spare, outspoken political folk that occupied singer/songwriters throughout the ’60s gave way to lush, mellifluous ballads and rowdy rave-ups in which artists examined matters of the heart and soul from multiple angles. Armed with little more than a six-string, poet/philosophers like Cat Stevens and Joni Mitchell helped listeners make sense of everyday chaos, while charismatic crooners like Billy Joel and Elton John sent worries scurrying away on a cascade of piano chords.\",\"short\":\"Mellow ballads and piano jams that view love and life from all angles.\"}}},{\"id\":\"pl.59e1f98bd0a04136b7177224aa043104\",\"type\":\"playlists\",\"href\":\"/v1/catalog/us/playlists/pl.59e1f98bd0a04136b7177224aa043104?l=en-US\",\"attributes\":{\"artwork\":{\"width\":1080,\"height\":1080,\"url\":\"https://is3-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Features124/v4/97/91/b6/9791b64c-8965-dc1d-39ff-ff7023f085b3/source/{w}x{h}SC.CAESS01.{f}?l=en-US\",\"bgColor\":\"f8eee5\",\"textColor1\":\"000000\",\"textColor2\":\"321f0c\",\"textColor3\":\"4d4331\",\"textColor4\":\"53402c\"},\"isChart\":false,\"url\":\"https://music.apple.com/us/playlist/folk-rock-essentials/pl.59e1f98bd0a04136b7177224aa043104\",\"lastModifiedDate\":\"2020-12-03T20:30:43Z\",\"name\":\"Folk Rock Essentials\",\"playlistType\":\"editorial\",\"curatorName\":\"Apple Music Classic Rock\",\"playParams\":{\"id\":\"pl.59e1f98bd0a04136b7177224aa043104\",\"kind\":\"playlist\"},\"editorialNotes\":{\"name\":\"Folk Rock Essentials\",\"standard\":\"Bob Dylan may have been branded a Judas-like traitor when he cranked up his amp during an infamous 1966 concert, but the rock ‘n’ roll undercurrents that infiltrated folk music in the ’60s didn’t betray the movement’s grassroots—they amplified the passion at its core. With the war in Vietnam entering its second decade, Buffalo Springfield and other protest singers traded six-string strumming for electrified riffs. The Byrds and Simon \u0026amp; Garfunkel added depth to jingle-jangle harmonies, while counterculture emissaries like The Mamas \u0026amp; The Papas and Jefferson Airplane offered fans new conduits to hippie bliss. This phenomenon wasn’t unique to North America: Across the Atlantic, Donovan and Fairport Convention fused troubadour-oriented tradition with the crackle of space-age technology. As the ’70s wore on, psychedelic grooves overshadowed folk convention and campfire intimacy morphed into radio-friendly soft-rock vibes, but the influence of plugged-in Dylan and his peers continues to this day.\",\"short\":\"Jangly guitars and introspective poetry that shaped '60s music.\"},\"description\":{\"standard\":\"Bob Dylan may have been branded a Judas-like traitor when he cranked up his amp during an infamous 1966 concert, but the rock ‘n’ roll undercurrents that infiltrated folk music in the ’60s didn’t betray the movement’s grassroots—they amplified the passion at its core. With the war in Vietnam entering its second decade, Buffalo Springfield and other protest singers traded six-string strumming for electrified riffs. The Byrds and Simon \u0026 Garfunkel added depth to jingle-jangle harmonies, while counterculture emissaries like The Mamas \u0026 The Papas and Jefferson Airplane offered fans new conduits to hippie bliss. This phenomenon wasn’t unique to North America: Across the Atlantic, Donovan and Fairport Convention fused troubadour-oriented tradition with the crackle of space-age technology. As the ’70s wore on, psychedelic grooves overshadowed folk convention and campfire intimacy morphed into radio-friendly soft-rock vibes, but the influence of plugged-in Dylan and his peers continues to this day.\",\"short\":\"Jangly guitars and introspective poetry that shaped '60s music.\"}}},{\"id\":\"pl.ad939de7c49249bbbd044d22a94e3487\",\"type\":\"playlists\",\"href\":\"/v1/catalog/us/playlists/pl.ad939de7c49249bbbd044d22a94e3487?l=en-US\",\"attributes\":{\"artwork\":{\"width\":1080,\"height\":1080,\"url\":\"https://is2-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Features128/v4/a1/29/a7/a129a744-e9dc-af67-30a7-9b5e5cd5fde3/source/{w}x{h}SC.DN01.{f}?l=en-US\",\"bgColor\":\"221817\",\"textColor1\":\"ffffff\",\"textColor2\":\"e0dfdf\",\"textColor3\":\"d2d0d0\",\"textColor4\":\"bab7b7\"},\"isChart\":false,\"url\":\"https://music.apple.com/us/playlist/tears-go-by/pl.ad939de7c49249bbbd044d22a94e3487\",\"lastModifiedDate\":\"2017-02-12T20:18:51Z\",\"name\":\"Tears Go By\",\"playlistType\":\"editorial\",\"curatorName\":\"Apple Music Rock\",\"playParams\":{\"id\":\"pl.ad939de7c49249bbbd044d22a94e3487\",\"kind\":\"playlist\"},\"editorialNotes\":{\"name\":\"Tears Go By\",\"standard\":\"A decade-spanning playlist of rock to get you through the hard times.\",\"short\":\"A decade-spanning playlist of rock to get you through the hard times.\"},\"description\":{\"standard\":\"A decade-spanning playlist of rock to get you through the hard times.\"}}},{\"id\":\"pl.55efa1bf16814bd8bafe2b46d31d3b55\",\"type\":\"playlists\",\"href\":\"/v1/catalog/us/playlists/pl.55efa1bf16814bd8bafe2b46d31d3b55?l=en-US\",\"attributes\":{\"artwork\":{\"width\":2400,\"height\":2400,\"url\":\"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music124/v4/3a/a4/0e/3aa40e2e-651a-0741-e5ba-db968f951d5b/source/{w}x{h}SC.FPESS02.{f}?l=en-US\",\"bgColor\":\"434343\",\"textColor1\":\"f8f8f8\",\"textColor2\":\"dfdfdf\",\"textColor3\":\"d4d4d4\",\"textColor4\":\"c0c0c0\"},\"isChart\":false,\"url\":\"https://music.apple.com/us/playlist/nick-drake-essentials/pl.55efa1bf16814bd8bafe2b46d31d3b55\",\"lastModifiedDate\":\"2019-09-20T05:47:38Z\",\"name\":\"Nick Drake Essentials\",\"playlistType\":\"editorial\",\"curatorName\":\"Apple Music Indie\",\"playParams\":{\"id\":\"pl.55efa1bf16814bd8bafe2b46d31d3b55\",\"kind\":\"playlist\"},\"editorialNotes\":{\"name\":\"Nick Drake Essentials\",\"standard\":\"English folk singer Nick Drake falls into the category of influential artists whose work was unfortunately underappreciated when it was first released. Putting out three albums of deeply affecting songs from 1969 to 1972 that explored his personal demons, Drake failed to find critical or commercial success before his death in 1974. Discovered posthumously by a bevy of artists, Drake's story and work found notoriety in the ‘90s before going on to be used in hit films like 2001's The Royal Tenenbaums and 2004's Garden State.\",\"short\":\"An all-too-brief career that influenced generations of folk singers.\"},\"description\":{\"standard\":\"English folk singer Nick Drake falls into the category of influential artists whose work was unfortunately underappreciated when it was first released. Putting out three albums of deeply affecting songs from 1969 to 1972 that explored his personal demons, Drake failed to find critical or commercial success before his death in 1974. Discovered posthumously by a bevy of artists, Drake's story and work found notoriety in the ‘90s before going on to be used in hit films like 2001's The Royal Tenenbaums and 2004's Garden State.\",\"short\":\"An all-too-brief career that influenced generations of folk singers.\"}}},{\"id\":\"pl.a99fc9cfcf554228a0795b5c54fde910\",\"type\":\"playlists\",\"href\":\"/v1/catalog/us/playlists/pl.a99fc9cfcf554228a0795b5c54fde910?l=en-US\",\"attributes\":{\"artwork\":{\"width\":1080,\"height\":1080,\"url\":\"https://is2-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Features114/v4/df/e4/8d/dfe48d6f-2d13-6da9-a88c-08e413155b53/source/{w}x{h}SC.CAESS01.{f}?l=en-US\",\"bgColor\":\"f7f0e6\",\"textColor1\":\"000000\",\"textColor2\":\"0d0c0c\",\"textColor3\":\"2d2d2b\",\"textColor4\":\"2f2d2c\"},\"isChart\":false,\"url\":\"https://music.apple.com/us/playlist/classic-singer-songwriter-essentials/pl.a99fc9cfcf554228a0795b5c54fde910\",\"lastModifiedDate\":\"2021-01-15T22:44:10Z\",\"name\":\"Classic Singer/Songwriter Essentials\",\"playlistType\":\"editorial\",\"curatorName\":\"Apple Music Acoustic\",\"playParams\":{\"id\":\"pl.a99fc9cfcf554228a0795b5c54fde910\",\"kind\":\"playlist\"},\"editorialNotes\":{\"name\":\"Classic Singer/Songwriter Essentials\",\"standard\":\"A melodious alchemy of words and music is the through line connecting these soul-stirring singer/songwriters who mostly rose to prominence in the late '60s and early '70s. None has been more influential than the freewheeling and ever-changing Bob Dylan. His folk roots, readiness to rock, and utterly unique poetic sensibility that extended from the dirt to the stars all inspired both Simon \u0026amp; Garfunkel’s harmonized melancholy and Neil Young's keening warmth. Like Young, Leonard Cohen and Joni Mitchell left Canada for California, the singer/songwriter movement’s seismic epicenter. The former’s battered baritone and stately Zen worldview stoked a long and majestic career, while the latter transformed the field with inventive guitar harmonies and a stunning sense of female independence. And Loudon Wainwright III, one of the more prominent \\\"new Dylans\\\" to emerge in the early '70s, and hardcore Angeleno Randy Newman proved that a biting sense of humor made even the most incendiary personal and political observations delicious.\",\"short\":\"The '60s kindled a melodious alchemy of words and music.\"},\"description\":{\"standard\":\"A melodious alchemy of words and music is the through line connecting these soul-stirring singer/songwriters who mostly rose to prominence in the late '60s and early '70s. None has been more influential than the freewheeling and ever-changing Bob Dylan. His folk roots, readiness to rock, and utterly unique poetic sensibility that extended from the dirt to the stars all inspired both Simon \u0026 Garfunkel’s harmonized melancholy and Neil Young's keening warmth. Like Young, Leonard Cohen and Joni Mitchell left Canada for California, the singer/songwriter movement’s seismic epicenter. The former’s battered baritone and stately Zen worldview stoked a long and majestic career, while the latter transformed the field with inventive guitar harmonies and a stunning sense of female independence. And Loudon Wainwright III, one of the more prominent \\\"new Dylans\\\" to emerge in the early '70s, and hardcore Angeleno Randy Newman proved that a biting sense of humor made even the most incendiary personal and political observations delicious.\",\"short\":\"The '60s kindled a melodious alchemy of words and music.\"}}},{\"id\":\"pl.f00394caa90e4114a93cebff2c7d5057\",\"type\":\"playlists\",\"href\":\"/v1/catalog/us/playlists/pl.f00394caa90e4114a93cebff2c7d5057?l=en-US\",\"attributes\":{\"artwork\":{\"width\":2400,\"height\":2400,\"url\":\"https://is5-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music124/v4/a3/39/cd/a339cd8c-39ec-b0ec-2741-835af35a7b37/source/{w}x{h}SC.FPINF01.{f}?l=en-US\",\"bgColor\":\"020514\",\"textColor1\":\"f8783a\",\"textColor2\":\"eb7733\",\"textColor3\":\"c76133\",\"textColor4\":\"bc602d\"},\"isChart\":false,\"url\":\"https://music.apple.com/us/playlist/kate-bush-influences/pl.f00394caa90e4114a93cebff2c7d5057\",\"lastModifiedDate\":\"2016-12-16T16:44:54Z\",\"name\":\"Kate Bush: Influences\",\"playlistType\":\"editorial\",\"curatorName\":\"Apple Music Pop\",\"playParams\":{\"id\":\"pl.f00394caa90e4114a93cebff2c7d5057\",\"kind\":\"playlist\"},\"editorialNotes\":{\"name\":\"Kate Bush: Influences\",\"standard\":\"The otherworldly elixir of artists who inspired Kate Bush's musical incantations brings together global folk, rock, mystical jazz, and the dreamiest, most captivating vocal melodies. Her gorgeous songs combine a heaping dose of strutting, androgynous glam (Elton John, T-Rex, David Bowie, Roxy Music) with equal parts prog wizardry (Jethro Tull, Peter Gabriel) and acoustic enchantment (Nick Drake, Laura Nyro, Joni Mitchell).\",\"short\":\"The otherworldly elixir behind her musical incantations.\"},\"description\":{\"standard\":\"The otherworldly elixir of artists who inspired Kate Bush's musical incantations brings together global folk, rock, mystical jazz, and the dreamiest, most captivating vocal melodies. Her gorgeous songs combine a heaping dose of strutting, androgynous glam (Elton John, T-Rex, David Bowie, Roxy Music) with equal parts prog wizardry (Jethro Tull, Peter Gabriel) and acoustic enchantment (Nick Drake, Laura Nyro, Joni Mitchell).\",\"short\":\"The otherworldly elixir behind her musical incantations.\"}}},{\"id\":\"pl.1042ceb945784dce84446f2c1616bded\",\"type\":\"playlists\",\"href\":\"/v1/catalog/us/playlists/pl.1042ceb945784dce84446f2c1616bded?l=en-US\",\"attributes\":{\"artwork\":{\"width\":2400,\"height\":2400,\"url\":\"https://is3-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music124/v4/3a/a4/0e/3aa40e2e-651a-0741-e5ba-db968f951d5b/source/{w}x{h}SC.FPNS01.{f}?l=en-US\",\"bgColor\":\"434343\",\"textColor1\":\"f8f8f8\",\"textColor2\":\"dfdfdf\",\"textColor3\":\"d4d4d4\",\"textColor4\":\"c0c0c0\"},\"isChart\":false,\"url\":\"https://music.apple.com/us/playlist/nick-drake-next-steps/pl.1042ceb945784dce84446f2c1616bded\",\"lastModifiedDate\":\"2019-09-20T05:49:14Z\",\"name\":\"Nick Drake: Next Steps\",\"playlistType\":\"editorial\",\"curatorName\":\"Apple Music Rock\",\"playParams\":{\"id\":\"pl.1042ceb945784dce84446f2c1616bded\",\"kind\":\"playlist\"},\"editorialNotes\":{\"name\":\"Nick Drake: Next Steps\",\"standard\":\"Folk singer Nick Drake was too idiosyncratic and haunting to capture a wide audience during his lifetime, but the shy and troubled genius has slowly earned a posthumous reputation as one of the most powerful singers of his era. If you've already been enchanted by Drake's hushed and pastoral songs, journey further into his world with this intimate, psychedelic, and evocative collection.\",\"short\":\"Melancholy and mystical folk gems from the singer's brief but captivating run.\"},\"description\":{\"standard\":\"Folk singer Nick Drake was too idiosyncratic and haunting to capture a wide audience during his lifetime, but the shy and troubled genius has slowly earned a posthumous reputation as one of the most powerful singers of his era. If you've already been enchanted by Drake's hushed and pastoral songs, journey further into his world with this intimate, psychedelic, and evocative collection.\",\"short\":\"Melancholy and mystical folk gems from the singer's brief but captivating run.\"}}},{\"id\":\"pl.4b36716c652d4a28867e8f5a61923bb1\",\"type\":\"playlists\",\"href\":\"/v1/catalog/us/playlists/pl.4b36716c652d4a28867e8f5a61923bb1?l=en-US\",\"attributes\":{\"artwork\":{\"width\":1027,\"height\":1027,\"url\":\"https://is5-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music124/v4/31/c0/9f/31c09f83-074b-9093-24ae-6be2025d7567/source/{w}x{h}SC.FPBTB01.{f}?l=en-US\",\"bgColor\":\"c6cfca\",\"textColor1\":\"150500\",\"textColor2\":\"540200\",\"textColor3\":\"382d28\",\"textColor4\":\"6b2b28\"},\"isChart\":false,\"url\":\"https://music.apple.com/us/playlist/behind-the-boards-joe-boyd/pl.4b36716c652d4a28867e8f5a61923bb1\",\"lastModifiedDate\":\"2015-04-11T16:11:37Z\",\"name\":\"Behind the Boards: Joe Boyd\",\"playlistType\":\"editorial\",\"curatorName\":\"Apple Music Classic Rock\",\"playParams\":{\"id\":\"pl.4b36716c652d4a28867e8f5a61923bb1\",\"kind\":\"playlist\"},\"editorialNotes\":{\"name\":\"Behind the Boards: Joe Boyd\",\"standard\":\"American expat Joe Boyd got his start in London's progressive folk and rock scene in 1966, with sides by Eric Clapton, Pink Floyd, and The Incredible String Band. By the time he started his Witchseason production company, he was the king of British folk-rock, helming classic albums by Nick Drake, John Martyn, and Fairport Convention. In later years, he worked with acts like R.E.M. and Billy Bragg.\",\"short\":\"Progressive British folk's finest producer.\"},\"description\":{\"standard\":\"American expat Joe Boyd got his start in London's progressive folk and rock scene in 1966, with sides by Eric Clapton, Pink Floyd, and The Incredible String Band. By the time he started his Witchseason production company, he was the king of British folk-rock, helming classic albums by Nick Drake, John Martyn, and Fairport Convention. In later years, he worked with acts like R.E.M. and Billy Bragg.\",\"short\":\"Progressive British folk's finest producer.\"}}},{\"id\":\"pl.674fe1f8d3d34f83b44bac9ed3fb2443\",\"type\":\"playlists\",\"href\":\"/v1/catalog/us/playlists/pl.674fe1f8d3d34f83b44bac9ed3fb2443?l=en-US\",\"attributes\":{\"artwork\":{\"width\":4320,\"height\":1080,\"url\":\"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Features114/v4/4d/9c/a4/4d9ca478-d4e3-a6c2-1303-9e8b38e41599/source/{w}x{h}cc.{f}\",\"bgColor\":\"fff9df\",\"textColor1\":\"321821\",\"textColor2\":\"27221e\",\"textColor3\":\"543b40\",\"textColor4\":\"4a453d\"},\"isChart\":false,\"url\":\"https://music.apple.com/us/playlist/lianne-la-havas-summer-bbq/pl.674fe1f8d3d34f83b44bac9ed3fb2443\",\"lastModifiedDate\":\"2020-07-22T16:42:06Z\",\"name\":\"Lianne La Havas' Summer BBQ\",\"playlistType\":\"editorial\",\"curatorName\":\"Apple Music\",\"playParams\":{\"id\":\"pl.674fe1f8d3d34f83b44bac9ed3fb2443\",\"kind\":\"playlist\"},\"editorialNotes\":{\"standard\":\"\\\"The music I wanna hear if I’m at a BBQ is the same music I wanna hear all year round,” Lianne La Havas tells Apple Music. For this exclusive summer playlist, the London folk-soul dynamo has chosen music from across the spectrum—Moses Sumney to Aretha Franklin to Nick Drake to Toro y Moi and Ethiopian jazz legend Mulatu Astatke. “Just my favorite tunes,” she says. “All. Day. All. Night. Cos’ my BBQs go late late.”\",\"short\":\"\\\"The music I wanna hear if I’m at a BBQ is the same music I wanna hear all year round.”\"},\"description\":{\"standard\":\"\\\"The music I wanna hear if I’m at a BBQ is the same music I wanna hear all year round,” Lianne La Havas tells Apple Music. For this exclusive summer playlist, the London folk-soul dynamo has chosen music from across the spectrum—Moses Sumney to Aretha Franklin to Nick Drake to Toro y Moi and Ethiopian jazz legend Mulatu Astatke. “Just my favorite tunes,” she says. “All. Day. All. Night. Cos’ my BBQs go late late.”\",\"short\":\"\\\"The music I wanna hear if I’m at a BBQ is the same music I wanna hear all year round.”\"}}},{\"id\":\"pl.c4aafdc457c3477380946d925eb1adf3\",\"type\":\"playlists\",\"href\":\"/v1/catalog/us/playlists/pl.c4aafdc457c3477380946d925eb1adf3?l=en-US\",\"attributes\":{\"artwork\":{\"width\":2160,\"height\":2160,\"url\":\"https://is2-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Music114/v4/0f/40/ba/0f40ba2e-a3bf-a450-b2dd-01c77d7e28c5/source/{w}x{h}SC.FPINF01.{f}?l=en-US\",\"bgColor\":\"043956\",\"textColor1\":\"d2d2ac\",\"textColor2\":\"b7c7dd\",\"textColor3\":\"a9b39b\",\"textColor4\":\"93abc2\"},\"isChart\":false,\"url\":\"https://music.apple.com/us/playlist/sufjan-stevens-influences/pl.c4aafdc457c3477380946d925eb1adf3\",\"lastModifiedDate\":\"2017-03-16T18:42:37Z\",\"name\":\"Sufjan Stevens: Influences\",\"playlistType\":\"editorial\",\"curatorName\":\"Apple Music Indie\",\"playParams\":{\"id\":\"pl.c4aafdc457c3477380946d925eb1adf3\",\"kind\":\"playlist\"},\"editorialNotes\":{\"name\":\"Sufjan Stevens: Influences\",\"standard\":\"Sufjan Stevens has drawn inspiration from the precision and emotional intelligence of songwriters like Elliott Smith and Nick Drake, as well as from the way artists like Brian Eno and Steve Reich build cathedrals of atmosphere to express feelings beyond words. In marrying the storyteller and composer parts of his brain into a balanced whole, Stevens used experimental-pop mavens like The Beach Boys and Stereolab as artistic goalposts.\",\"short\":\"Mixing a classical, folky intimacy with avant-garde eccentricity.\"},\"description\":{\"standard\":\"Sufjan Stevens has drawn inspiration from the precision and emotional intelligence of songwriters like Elliott Smith and Nick Drake, as well as from the